div1.ab: In Justice's Court. - Before T.H. Cann, Justice of the Peace
Territory of Washington, Plaintiff vs. George E Daly Defendant | Territory of Washington, County of King. - ss.
To the Sheriff or any Constable of said County, Greeting:
div1.p: Whereas, J.H. Woolery has this day complained in writing, under oath, to the undersigned, one of the Justices of the Peace in and for said County, that on the day of 1884, at Oregon in said County said deft did felounously steal + take away one horse of the value of $50 set forth in camper
div1.ab: Therefore, in the name of the United States, you are commanded forthwith to apprehend the said deft and bring him before me, to be dealt with according to law
Given under my hand this 11 day of March 1884.
TH Cann Justice of the Peace, Seattle Precinct, King County, W.T.
